{"id":14880805,"mediaExerciseId":"95c5aaef-0404-419d-a45c-981f853f3686","exerciseName":"10","chapterName":"3","chapterTitle":"Working with Financial Statements","groupId":612275,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":86,"solutions":[{"id":5962860,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to determine how long it took, on average, for the company to pay off its suppliers during the year.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/bad443be71022ca0c9b265bd78b5eef6/913c1a789a7746f2b8c9e01f2eefec32/lateximg_large.png","width":994},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/bad443be71022ca0c9b265bd78b5eef6/913c1a789a7746f2b8c9e01f2eefec32/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first days' payable outstanding.\n\n**Days' payable outstanding or DPO** measures how long it takes the company to pay its suppliers.\n\nThe formula is denoted as follows:\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{DPO}& =\n \\dfrac{\\text{Accounts Payable}} {\\text{Cost of Goods Sold}} \\times \\text{365 days}\\\\ \\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":231,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/bad443be71022ca0c9b265bd78b5eef6/caab0473a9fee0e5f3c2ed9ff70209d4/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":118,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/bad443be71022ca0c9b265bd78b5eef6/caab0473a9fee0e5f3c2ed9ff70209d4/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"To determine the days' payable outstanding for Heritage, Inc.:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{DPO}& =\n \\dfrac{\\text{Accounts Payable}} {\\text{Cost of Goods Sold}} \\times \\text{365 days}\\\\ \\\\\n& = \\frac{\\$15,486} {\\$68,314} \\times365\\\\ \\\\\n&= \\boxed{82.74}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\\\nIn conclusion, it took **82.74** days on average for the company to pay off its suppliers during the year.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":442,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/bad443be71022ca0c9b265bd78b5eef6/45c87f5491da6b942a49df7accc4175b/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":222,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/bad443be71022ca0c9b265bd78b5eef6/45c87f5491da6b942a49df7accc4175b/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"A large value for this ratio might imply that the company have better credit terms compared to their competitors or they are unable to pay their bills on time. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":97,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/bad443be71022ca0c9b265bd78b5eef6/9e169bf3f019009ed0d8045ef4526d6d/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":50,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/bad443be71022ca0c9b265bd78b5eef6/9e169bf3f019009ed0d8045ef4526d6d/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"fdb0ba7c-9236-4639-86f6-4cc772075ecd","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"mod